properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail - PARRAMATTA Church Street between Factory Street, North Parramatta AND Macquarie Street
properties.otherAdvice:
The following changed traffic conditions are in place until the operational launch of the Parramatta Light Rail:

  • Church St is closed to traffic in both directions.
  • There is no access to Church St from the eastern side of Albert St.
  • There is no access to Church St from the western side of Factory St, Harold St, Fennell St, or Ross St.
properties.diversions: Motorists should use O’Connell St to travel across Parramatta during this time.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Parramatta Light Rail

properties.headline: HAZARD Slope instability/debris - HAMPTON Jenolan Caves Road between Old Bindo Road AND Duckmaloi Road, Oberon
properties.otherAdvice:

Jenolan Caves Rd remains closed at Jenolan.
properties.diversions: For vehicles wider than 3m: Great Western Hwy to Bathurst then O’Connell Rd to Oberon.

properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Rail bridge replacement - WALLENDBEEN Burley Griffin Way between Silo Road AND North Jindalee Road
properties.otherAdvice:
The bridge has reopened with a single lane operating under portable traffic lights, so vehicles can pass in one direction at a time.

There is a 4.2m width restriction on the bridge.
properties.diversions:
Vehicles over 4.2m wide:
Eastbound: From Temora - Goldfields Way to Junee, then the Olympic Hwy to Wallendbeen.
Westbound: From Wallendbeen - Olympic Hwy to Junee, then Goldfields Way to Temora.

This route will add around 40 minutes to your travel time.
properties.displayName: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS Rail bridge replacement
